Package: xul-ext-compactheader
Source: compactheader
Version: 2.1.6-1
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Debian Mozilla Extension Maintainers <pkg-mozext-maintainers@alioth-lists.debian.net>
Installed-Size: 545
Depends: thunderbird (>= 1:52.0) | icedove (>= 1:52.0)
Enhances: icedove, thunderbird
Breaks: icedove (<< 1:52.0), thunderbird (<< 1:52.0)
Provides: compactheader, icedove-compactheader, thunderbird-compactheader
Section: mail
Priority: optional
Homepage: http://compactheader.mozdev.org/
Description: Thunderbird extension to reduce header size to one or two lines
 compactheader adds a button to compact Thunderbird’s header pane to a single
 line or expand it again. It also allows the user to disable the new
 buttons that Thunderbird 3 added to the header pane.
 This add-on integrates the functionality of "RSS Linkify Subject"
 by Alex Dedul.
 https://addons.mozilla.org/thunderbird/addon/rss-linkify-subject/
